The paper presents a deep learning framework for ultrasound elastography, which involves the inversion of sound speed measurements to diagnose medical conditions. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves image analysis and interpretation. The use of deep neural networks for sound speed inversion also falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also involves simulations and data analysis, which could fall under statistical learning (cs.SD). Finally, the application of the technology is in the field of medical imaging (cs.BIO).
